! Managed by the desktop role (tasks/idle.yml). Appearance of the xscreensaver unlock dialog.
!
! These are X resources, not ~/.xscreensaver preferences: xscreensaver-auth (Xt) merges
! RESOURCE_MANAGER over its app-defaults, and the bspwm session script runs
! `xrdb -merge ~/.Xresources`. (dialogTheme is the exception, a preference idle.yml writes to
! ~/.xscreensaver.) Set individual resources, not the whole app-defaults file.
!
! What is removed is everything but the prompt: hostname, clock, "New Login" button and
! thermometer. The logo and version heading stay (xscreensaver aborts without the logo, and
! the author asks that the heading not be removed).
*passwd.uname:	False
*dateFormat:
*newLoginCommand:
*{{ desktop_xscreensaver_dialog_theme }}.Dialog.thermometer.width:	0
